# Mirror source of truth

**griddungeon-game** `Assets/Scripts/Core/` is canonical. **griddungeon-core** `src/` is an export snapshot.

## Edit where

| Change type | Repo | Then |
|---|---|---|
| Simulators, DTOs, save shapes, maze gen, Core rules | **griddungeon-game** `Assets/Scripts/Core/` | Run `./scripts/sync-from-game.ps1` here |
| `.csproj`, CI, README, Cursor config, sync script | **griddungeon-core** | Commit in this repo only |
| Campaign/story behavior, Unity Runtime/UI | **griddungeon-game** `Campaign/` / `Runtime/` | Out of mirror scope |

## Do not

- Implement new game rules **only** under `src/` in this repo (drifts from game; next sync overwrites or diverges).
- Add `.meta`, `.asmdef`, `UnityEngine`, or `MonoBehaviour` to `src/`.
- Run sync scripts that **write** into griddungeon-game from this repo.

## Sync workflow

1. Merge Core change in game repo.
2. From **this repo** root: `./scripts/sync-from-game.ps1`
3. `dotnet build -c Release`
4. Commit mirror: `sync: mirror Core from griddungeon-game @ <sha>`

Skill: `.cursor/skills/sync-from-game/SKILL.md`.

## Agent default

When user asks to **add/fix Core logic**: implement in **griddungeon-game** (unless user explicitly scopes mirror-only scaffolding). Remind to sync after game merge.

When user asks to **update mirror** or **sync**: run `sync-from-game.ps1` only — no game repo edits.
